14/06/2007
ANKARA, Turkey -- Top government and army representatives reaffirmed that fighting terrorism remains a top priority for the country, during an emergency security summit in Ankara late Tuesday (June 12th).
The meeting focused mostly on action against the terror organisation Kurdistan Workers Party (PKK).
According to local press reports, participants agreed on the deployment of specially trained squads in the country's southern provinces.
The squads would apply new methods against the PKK there.
(Zaman, Milliyet - 14/06/07;
NTV - 13/06/07)
